27/03/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The last 2,500 conscripts were recruited by the army on Monday (March 26th).
They will serve for nine months, with the option to continue on after that.
The military expects 30% to decide to become career soldiers.
Bulgaria's Land Forces are scheduled to become fully professional by January 1st 2008, bringing an end to mandatory military service.
(Sega, 24 Chasa - 27/03/07;
Mediapool, bTV - 26/03/07)
